article.headline: Bowling Green 77, Georgia St. 76
article.story: MINNEAPOLIS -- Joe Jakubowski's 3-pointer at the buzzer gave Bowling Green a 77-76 overtime victory over Georgia St. in the opening game of the NABC Classic Friday at Williams Arena. Jakubowski finished with 24 points for the Falcons, going 6-for-8 from beyond the 3-point line. Brian Moten added 19, including a 3-pointer to put the game into overtime. Erik Marshall scored 17 points, six in the extra session, and grabbed nine rebounds. Joe Dukes scored 20 points and had 12 rebounds for Georgia State. Xavier Hansbro scored 16 and Leonard Mendez added 15. Dukes had put the Panthers ahead 76-74 grabbing a rebound off his own missed shot and following with a lay-up. The NABC Classic is a three-day, round-robin tournament hosted by Minnesota.
